headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 28 points and 12 rebounds, and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Brooklyn Nets 123-94 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid powers 76ers to a 123-94 victory over the short-handed Nets

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 27 points and Myles Turner added 20 points, six rebounds and three blocks, leading the Indiana Pacers past the Phoenix Suns 126-108 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Haliburton scores 27 to help Pacers reach .500 with a 126-108 victory over the Suns

headlines.description: — Brice Sensabaugh scored a career-high 34 points, John Collins finished with 24, and the Utah Jazz snapped a five-game losing streak with a 136-100 rout over the Miami Heat on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sensabaugh scores career-high 34, Jazz rout Heat 136-100

events.name: New York Knicks at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Coby White made a career-high nine 3-pointers and scored 33 points, Zach LaVine also had 33 and the Chicago Bulls beat the New York Knicks 139-126 after <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: White nails career-high nine 3s, scores 33 as Bulls beat Knicks 139-126 after honoring Rose

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 28 points and Deni Avdija 19 as the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Milwaukee Bucks 105-102 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anfernee Simons and Deni Avdija power the Trail Blazers past the Bucks 105-102

events.name: Denver Nuggets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 46 points and 10 rebounds and the Denver Nuggets spoiled Victor Wembanyama’s 21st birthday on Saturday, beating the San Antonio Spurs 122-111 in overtime.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic and Nuggets beat the Spurs 122-111 in overtime to spoil Wembanyama's 21st birthday

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Andrew Wiggins scored 24 points, Dennis Schroder added 17 and the undermanned Golden State Warriors held off the Memphis Grizzlies 121-113 on Saturday night in the latest testy matchup between the rivals.
headlines.shortLinkText: Andrew Wiggins scores 24 points as undermanned Warriors missing Stephen Curry beat Memphis 121-113

headlines.description: — Norman Powell scored 20 points, Kawhi Leonard added 12 in his first game of the season and the Los Angeles Clippers rolled to a 131-105 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell scores 20, Leonard has 12 points in return as Clippers cruise to 131-105 victory over Hawks
